 ---------------------------Dear Bruce,There are a lot of preconcieved notions of what remote (aka, "telecommuting") jobs can be, and quite honestly, most of them are outdated. While 15 years ago it was true that most remote jobs 15 or more years ago were limited to writing, programming, sales, and other specific niche jobs, nowadays, you can find a remote job in almost any industry ( https://www.flexjobs.com?utm_campaign=website&utm_source=sendgrid.com&utm_medium=email/jobs?utm_campaign=website&utm_source=sendgrid.com&utm_medium=email?utm_campaign=website&utm_source=sendgrid.com&utm_medium=email?utm_campaign=website&utm_source=sendgrid.com&utm_medium=email ), ranging from entry-level to executive, part-time to full-time! To highlight this, we compiled this list of 100 of the Most Surprising Flexible Jobs, 50 Past and 50 Present, ( https://www.flexjobs.com/jobs/surprising-jobs?utm_campaign=website&utm_source=sendgrid.com&utm_medium=email ) in order to help showcase that flexible work - meaning remote, freelance, part-time, flexible, and alternative schedule jobs - offers far more viable professional options than most people tend to realize. Check them out to see if any of them cause you to raise your eyebrows. :-) Relatedly, here are 15 Statistics About Telecommuting in the U.S. ( https://www.flexjobs.com/blog/post/stats-about-telecommuting-in-the-us/?utm_campaign=website&utm_source=sendgrid.com&utm_medium=email ) that most people might not realize, including expected growth, current telecommuting levels, and some of the best benefits of these kinds of work situations. We really want to help everyone get a better sense of the big picture, and why not only is it such a benefit to workers and to employers, but also why remote work is a much more viable professional option now than ever before. As always, thank you so much for trusting us to help in your job search for great remote, freelance, part-time and flexible schedule opportunities ( https://www.flexjobs.com/jobs ). And if you choose to try our premium service to give yourself a leg up, be sure to enter promo code "NEWSLETTER" to get up to 30% off! We hope you have a wonderful rest of the week!Many cheers,Sara and the FlexJobs Team >>> https://www.flexjobs.com/FlexJobsTeam.aspx?utm_campaign=website&utm_source=sendgrid.com&utm_medium=email---------------------------Enter This Month's Mini-Scavenger Hunt ContestEnter this month's contest to win one of ten 3-month FlexJobs subscriptions! This contest is a bit different than others, and involves a mini-scavenger hunt. To enter, you'll watch a short video to discover the question you'll need to answer and submit. Then go to our contest blog post and submit your answer in the comments at the bottom. Have fun, and hope you win!Enter This Month's Mini-Scavenger Hunt Contest! > >>> www.flexjobs.com/blog/post/contest-how-would-or-does-work-flexibility-improve-your-summer ---------------------------6 Go-To Email Subject Lines for Job Inquiriesiring managers often ask job candidates how much they make in their current position, which sets up a potentially awkward situation if an interviewee would rather not say. Applicants refusing to answer come off as uncooperative, but providing such information could hurt future earning potential.Check Out These 6 Go-To Email Subject Lines for Job Inquiries > >>> https://www.flexjobs.com/bhttps://www.flexjobs.com/blog/post/5-go-email-subject-lines-job-seekers/log/post/how-talk-about-salary-job-interview/?utm_campaign=website&utm_source=sendgrid.com&utm_medium=email ---------------------------30 People Share How Work Flexibility Changed Their Life for the BetterFor some, work flexibility is a want. For others, it’s a need. And for the majority of people, it’s both. To better showcase exactly how work flexibility can positively impact various facets of your life, we looked through dozens of responses on this topic from job seekers who have had success finding employment through FlexJobs. Check them 